03:02.883 --> 03:05.551
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: first
time I met sam barns</i>

03:05.553 --> 03:07.419
<i>I was 10 years old.</i>

03:07.421 --> 03:08.787
<i>(DOGS HOWLS)</i>

03:08.789 --> 03:10.255
come on, boy, come on.

03:10.257 --> 03:12.591
Whatcha got, boy?

03:12.593 --> 03:14.293
<i>(PANTING)</i>

03:14.295 --> 03:16.528
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: it was
the summer of 1929.</i>

03:16.530 --> 03:18.463
<i>And while I didn't
realize it then...</i>

03:18.465 --> 03:20.399
OFFICER: atta boy,
atta boy.

03:20.401 --> 03:23.335
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: it would lead
to the adventure of a lifetime.</i>

03:24.605 --> 03:26.271
OFFICER: come on, boys!

03:26.273 --> 03:28.674
He's gonna go
down on foot.

03:28.676 --> 03:32.277
<i>(TRAIN WHISTLES
IN THE DISTANCE)</i>

03:32.279 --> 03:34.346
everybody keep
their eyes peeled.

03:35.649 --> 03:38.784
<i>(DOGS BARKING,
GETTING CLOSER)</i>

03:38.786 --> 03:40.686
<i>♪ (SUSPENSE) ♪</i>

03:40.688 --> 03:42.454
<i>(DOG HOWLS)</i>

03:43.724 --> 03:46.425
hey, we got something
downstream here.

03:46.427 --> 03:50.262
<i>♪ (SUSPENSE) ♪</i>

03:50.264 --> 03:51.630
whatcha
got, boy?

03:51.632 --> 03:56.802
<i>(DOG PANTING)</i>

03:56.804 --> 04:00.439
come on,
boy, come on.

04:00.441 --> 04:02.741
<i>(DOG HOWLS)
(OTHER DOG BARKS)</i>

04:02.743 --> 04:04.476
<i>OFFICER: hey,
over here!</i>

04:04.478 --> 04:06.511
<i>I think we got
something!</i>

04:08.382 --> 04:13.418
<i>(DOGS BARK FADES)</i>

04:14.355 --> 04:23.629
<i>(TRAIN WHISTLES)</i>

04:23.631 --> 04:33.605
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:35.843 --> 04:37.609
<i>(ROOSTER CROWS)</i>

04:37.611 --> 04:46.818
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:46.820 --> 04:50.622
<i>(DOG PLAYFULLY GROWLS)</i>

04:50.624 --> 04:54.026
<i>(LAUGHS)</i>
okay pat, I'm up.

04:54.028 --> 04:56.295
<i>(DOG BARKS)</i>

04:56.297 --> 04:59.831
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:59.833 --> 05:03.769
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: it'd been over
a year since my father had died.</i>

05:03.771 --> 05:05.470
<i>I don't think my mother
had spent a night</i>

05:05.472 --> 05:06.838
<i>in their bed since.</i>

05:06.840 --> 05:12.544
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:12.546 --> 05:14.946
<i>mama was a strong woman.</i>

05:14.948 --> 05:17.983
<i>But, pain and loss have a way
of catching up to all of us.</i>

05:17.985 --> 05:22.754
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:22.756 --> 05:24.756
<i>it's strange how life works.</i>

05:26.760 --> 05:29.661
<i>My father had survived the war
to end all wars, only to meet</i>

05:29.663 --> 05:33.532
<i>his end from something as
random as a farming accident.</i>

05:33.534 --> 05:35.934
<i>It didn't seem fair.</i>

05:35.936 --> 05:39.338
<i>The void it caused in our life
couldn't be measured in words.</i>

05:39.340 --> 05:41.340
<i>(CROW SQUAWKING)</i>

05:41.342 --> 05:43.408
<i>dad had always been my hero.</i>

05:43.410 --> 05:46.411
<i>And when that hero was lost,
well...</i>

05:46.413 --> 05:48.046
<i>it seemed as though
a part of my mama and me</i>

05:48.048 --> 05:49.581
<i>were lost with him.</i>

05:49.583 --> 05:52.351
<i>(OPENING LETTER)</i>

05:52.353 --> 05:55.387
<i>life without dad
just wasn't the same.</i>

05:55.389 --> 05:58.957
<i>Aside from me not having
a pa and ma, a husband,</i>

05:58.959 --> 06:02.594
<i>his passing had left us at
a considerable disadvantage</i>

06:02.596 --> 06:04.396
<i>with the local bank.</i>

06:04.398 --> 06:06.998
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:07.000 --> 06:09.134
<i>SUSAN: tommy, I need you
to walk into town for me.</i>

06:09.136 --> 06:11.470
Give this envelope to
mr. Davis at the bank.

06:11.472 --> 06:12.971
You tell him it's all I can
come up with at the moment,

06:12.973 --> 06:15.574
but... I'll get him the rest
as soon as we get those

06:15.576 --> 06:16.875
horses broke and off to market.

06:16.877 --> 06:18.477
Okay, mama.

06:18.479 --> 06:20.045
And then, I want you to make
your way through town,

06:20.047 --> 06:24.082
put one of these fliers up on
any posting board you can find.

06:24.084 --> 06:27.386
We're gonna let people
live with us now?

06:27.388 --> 06:29.454
Well, unless you got a
better idea of how to pay

06:29.456 --> 06:31.923
the bank note on the farm.

06:31.925 --> 06:33.658
Guess not.

06:34.995 --> 06:37.662
That mean I'm gonna have
to share my room now?

06:37.664 --> 06:40.432
<i>(SIGHS)</i>
no, honey...

06:40.434 --> 06:42.434
you ain't gonna have
to share your room.

06:42.436 --> 06:43.769
All right, this is only
for the two spares.

06:43.771 --> 06:45.670
And this is only temporary.

06:45.672 --> 06:47.606
Just until we can get
back on our feet.

06:49.510 --> 06:50.876
Run along.
<i>(SMOOCH)</i>

06:50.878 --> 06:52.844
I need you back by lunch.

06:52.846 --> 06:54.079
Those horses ain't gonna
break themselves.

06:54.081 --> 06:56.481
TOMMY:
all right.

06:56.483 --> 07:00.051
<i>(DOOR CLOSES)
(SIGHS)</i>

07:00.053 --> 07:04.523
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: mama sure loved that
farm and everything it represented.</i>

07:04.525 --> 07:08.193
<i>It was the only thing of dad
she had left to hold onto.</i>

07:08.195 --> 07:11.897
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:11.899 --> 07:15.534
<i>our town was small, familiar,
and the only thing I knew</i>

07:15.536 --> 07:18.069
<i>of the world outside
of our little farm.</i>

07:18.071 --> 07:21.473
<i>I loved every chance
I had to visit.</i>

07:21.475 --> 07:24.609
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:28.882 --> 07:30.949
MR. DAVIS:
yes, young man?

07:30.951 --> 07:32.584
What can I do for ya?

07:32.586 --> 07:35.554
My ma said I was
to give this to you.

07:35.556 --> 07:38.657
You're the tilwicky
boy, right?

07:38.659 --> 07:39.858
<i>TOMMY: yes, sir.</i>

07:39.860 --> 07:42.194
I was told to tell
you Mr. Davis, um...

07:42.196 --> 07:45.130
that that money there is
all mama and me could get

07:45.132 --> 07:47.132
together for the time being.

07:47.134 --> 07:49.201
But that, we'd get you more
just as soon as she gets

07:49.203 --> 07:51.236
our horses broke
and off to market.

07:55.008 --> 07:57.609
Just tell your mama come
on by here and see me

07:57.611 --> 07:59.778
in the next few
days, all right?

07:59.780 --> 08:01.713
Yeah,
all right.

08:01.715 --> 08:11.623
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:11.625 --> 08:21.500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:21.502 --> 08:25.504
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:25.506 --> 08:30.609
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:32.546 --> 08:34.212
<i>TOMMY: morning,
Mr. Kinsley!</i>

08:34.214 --> 08:36.147
Good morning
to you, tommy!

08:36.149 --> 08:39.217
I was wondering if you had any
new books for me to look at.

08:39.219 --> 08:40.952
Hold on.

08:43.155 --> 08:45.724
<i>♪ (EPIC) ♪</i>

08:45.726 --> 08:47.058
now this...

08:47.060 --> 08:49.828
is a good one.

08:49.830 --> 08:52.564
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: "the
legend of five mile cave."</i>

08:52.566 --> 08:54.766
<i>I couldn't take my eyes off it.</i>

08:54.768 --> 08:57.869
<i>The story of the outlaw,
shooter green.</i>

08:57.871 --> 09:00.672
Thanks,
Mr. Kinsley.

09:00.674 --> 09:02.941
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: I just stared
at it the whole way back.</i>

09:02.943 --> 09:04.876
<i>I couldn't wait to get
home and read stories of</i>

09:04.878 --> 09:07.646
<i>gunslingers, daring horse
chases and the amazing</i>

09:07.648 --> 09:09.648
<i>adventures of the wild west.</i>

09:09.650 --> 09:13.318
<i>It opened up a whole new world
I didn't even know existed.</i>

09:13.320 --> 09:17.622
<i>Little did I know that this
book and a new stranger</i>

09:17.624 --> 09:20.792
<i>would take me on my
own daring adventure.</i>

09:20.794 --> 09:22.327
<i>(HORSE WHINNIES)</i>

09:24.264 --> 09:26.164
<i>we never know where
hope is going to come from.</i>

09:26.166 --> 09:28.166
Just a little
nervous, that's all.

09:28.168 --> 09:30.101
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: but that
day, hope came in two ways.</i>

09:30.103 --> 09:32.170
Come on,
come on.

09:32.172 --> 09:35.040
<i>Mama always said we needed
to have hope, even if we didn't</i>

09:35.042 --> 09:37.208
<i>know where it was coming from.</i>

09:37.210 --> 09:39.978
<i>But that day hope
came for both of us.</i>

09:40.914 --> 09:42.714
<i>SAM: good boy.</i>

09:42.716 --> 09:44.149
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: you see, mama
never had the knack</i>

09:44.151 --> 09:46.151
<i>for breaking
horses and she was having</i>

09:46.153 --> 09:48.620
<i>a difficult time getting
them ready for market.</i>

09:49.690 --> 09:52.090
Good boy,
good boy.

09:52.092 --> 09:54.826
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: and that was the
day sam barnes entered our lives.</i>

09:54.828 --> 09:58.063
SAM: whoa, whoa...
okay, okay.

09:58.065 --> 09:59.731
Go on, go on.

09:59.733 --> 10:01.866
Whoa, go on.

10:03.337 --> 10:05.170
You'll need to ride him
a few times a day for

10:05.172 --> 10:06.605
the next week or so.

10:06.607 --> 10:08.807
He'll handle nicely.

10:08.809 --> 10:12.210
You must
ride a lot.

10:12.212 --> 10:14.112
Well...

10:14.114 --> 10:15.981
a bit, Mrs. Tilwicky.

10:15.983 --> 10:18.149
It's been a while, but
a man never forgets.

10:18.151 --> 10:20.385
How do you
know my name?

10:20.387 --> 10:22.721
Ah, there's a fella up
the road selling supplies.

10:22.723 --> 10:24.823
Mr. Kinsley?
<i>SAM: yeah, he told me.</i>

10:24.825 --> 10:26.992
He said you were
accepting boarders?

10:26.994 --> 10:29.694
Tommy, why don't you
go feed the chickens?

10:29.696 --> 10:32.897
Go on, go on.
Okay, mama.

10:32.899 --> 10:34.933
<i>SAM: if that's not right,
I can be on my way.</i>

10:34.935 --> 10:37.736
No, no, that's--
That's right.

10:37.738 --> 10:38.937
You'll have to forgive
me, I've just got a lot

10:38.939 --> 10:41.039
on my mind is all.

10:41.041 --> 10:42.841
Susan tilwicky.

10:42.843 --> 10:44.676
That there's
my boy tommy.

10:46.813 --> 10:48.913
Sam, barnes.

10:48.915 --> 10:50.415
<i>SUSAN: nice to meet
you, Mr. Barnes.</i>

10:50.417 --> 10:52.117
Nice to meet you too.

10:52.119 --> 10:54.653
So... The room rate
is a dollar a night.

10:54.655 --> 10:58.056
That includes three squares
a day and fresh linens weekly.

10:58.058 --> 11:00.425
Uh, I don't uh...

11:00.427 --> 11:03.428
I don't exactly have
the rate you're asking.

11:03.430 --> 11:06.398
I was hoping I could...

11:06.400 --> 11:10.201
work off my keep, till I
find a regular paying job.

11:10.203 --> 11:12.771
I'm sure your husband
could use the help.

11:12.773 --> 11:14.973
My husband passed
near a year ago.

11:14.975 --> 11:16.908
It's just me
and tommy now.

11:16.910 --> 11:19.411
Oh, well I'm sorry
I-- I didn't know.

11:19.413 --> 11:21.179
<i>SUSAN: oh,
no matter.</i>

11:21.181 --> 11:24.749
Tommy's near a man
and he does real good.

11:24.751 --> 11:28.153
But... I'm afraid we're not
in a position to have anyone

11:28.155 --> 11:30.822
else on with us at the moment
unless it's on a paying basis.

11:30.824 --> 11:33.124
I-- I hope you
understand.

11:33.126 --> 11:34.726
Yes ma'am.

11:35.462 --> 11:37.829
I understand.

11:37.831 --> 11:40.231
I'll be uh...
on my way.

11:42.903 --> 11:44.869
Good luck with
those horses.

11:47.374 --> 11:49.841
<i>(HORSES WHINNY)</i>

11:56.483 --> 11:58.249
mr. Barnes!

11:58.251 --> 12:00.151
<i>Mr. Barnes!</i>

12:03.323 --> 12:07.358
Well, we do have a room in
the back of the barn with a cot.

12:07.360 --> 12:10.061
My husband used to stay
there when a cow was calving.

12:10.063 --> 12:11.996
So...

12:11.998 --> 12:15.366
you can stay there if you'd like
on a temporary basis, of course.

12:15.368 --> 12:17.268
But, you help us get these
horses broke and we'll

12:17.270 --> 12:20.905
talk about more suitable
accommodations inside.

12:20.907 --> 12:23.508
You got yourself
a deal.

12:23.510 --> 12:25.877
All right then,
all right then.

12:25.879 --> 12:27.278
I'll show you
to your room.

12:27.280 --> 12:36.955
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:37.891 --> 12:39.324
<i>(CHICKENS CLUCKING)</i>

12:41.061 --> 12:44.262
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: and that's
how we met sam barnes.</i>

12:44.264 --> 12:46.364
<i>I took a liking
to him right away.</i>

12:46.366 --> 12:48.800
<i>Mama was a little hesitant;</i>

12:48.802 --> 12:51.202
<i>as all good mothers are.</i>

12:51.204 --> 12:56.207
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:56.209 --> 13:05.450
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:05.452 --> 13:06.918
<i>SUSAN: dinner's ready.</i>

13:06.920 --> 13:12.190
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:12.192 --> 13:14.192
<i>SAM: that picture
in there, is--</i>

13:14.194 --> 13:16.094
Is that your mama?

13:17.497 --> 13:19.030
Oh, who, josie?

13:19.032 --> 13:21.332
No, no...

13:21.334 --> 13:25.370
she was a friend of my family
from a time in arizona.

13:25.372 --> 13:29.140
Unfortunately, she and her
child died during childbirth.

13:29.142 --> 13:30.475
I see.

13:30.477 --> 13:32.277
<i>SUSAN: yeah, sad.</i>

13:32.279 --> 13:34.979
You know, my mama always
kept that photograph around.

13:34.981 --> 13:38.016
She said it reminded her
of how lucky her and my pa

13:38.018 --> 13:40.084
were that I turned
out all right.

13:40.086 --> 13:42.253
And how fragile
life can be.

13:42.255 --> 13:43.822
That you did.

13:43.824 --> 13:46.925
Well, Mr. Barnes
would you...

13:46.927 --> 13:48.459
like to do the honors?

13:48.461 --> 13:50.261
Oh... I would.

13:50.263 --> 13:51.462
<i>(SILVERWARE CLANKS)</i>

13:51.464 --> 13:53.231
<i>(CLEARS THROAT)</i>

13:53.233 --> 13:55.834
uh, would you like
to lead us in prayer?

13:58.905 --> 14:01.339
If it's all the same to you,
I would prefer to leave it in

14:01.341 --> 14:03.508
your more than capable hands,
if that's all right.

14:03.510 --> 14:05.510
Very well.

14:06.513 --> 14:12.517
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:12.519 --> 14:17.522
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:17.524 --> 14:19.591
<i>SUSAN: dear lord, thank
you for the food that has</i>

14:19.593 --> 14:21.626
<i>been placed before us.</i>

14:21.628 --> 14:24.495
<i>Give us strength so that we
may help others who are less</i>

14:24.497 --> 14:28.032
<i>fortunate and help us to
find our way when we are</i>

14:28.034 --> 14:29.968
<i>blind to your cause.</i>

14:29.970 --> 14:34.339
<i>We ask all this in jesus
christ's name our savior, amen.</i>

14:34.341 --> 14:36.241
<i>Amen.</i>

14:36.243 --> 14:39.878
Now, Mr. Barnes, you
may do the honors.

14:39.880 --> 14:41.246
All right.

14:41.248 --> 14:42.981
There you go.

14:42.983 --> 14:47.552
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:47.554 --> 14:50.121
<i>OLDER TOMMY, V/O: now pulp
novels are a thing of the past.</i>

14:50.123 --> 14:54.125
<i>I spent hour after hour on that
porch, riding with jesse james</i>

14:54.127 --> 14:57.595
<i>and laughing with
calamity jane.</i>

14:57.597 --> 14:59.898
<i>When I turned a page...</i>

14:59.900 --> 15:03.067
<i>everything around me faded
away.</i>

15:03.069 --> 15:05.536
<i>How I wanted to truly be there.</i>

15:05.538 --> 15:08.673
<i>And through
those novels...</i>

15:08.675 --> 15:09.641
<i>I was.</i>

15:09.643 --> 15:16.147
<i>(GALLOPING SLOWLY)</i>

15:16.149 --> 15:18.182
<i>SAM: "the legend of
five mile cave."</i>

15:18.184 --> 15:20.985
the story of the outlaw,
shooter green.

15:20.987 --> 15:22.153
Sounds exciting.

15:22.155 --> 15:23.955
It is.

15:23.957 --> 15:26.624
This fella shooter, he pulled
off one of the greatest

15:26.626 --> 15:29.360
stagecoach robberies
the west had ever seen.

15:29.362 --> 15:32.664
They say he was as fast
with a gun as billy the kid.

15:32.666 --> 15:34.599
Billy the kid, you say?

15:34.601 --> 15:36.634
Yep.
SAM: that's fast.

15:36.636 --> 15:38.636
That's real fast.

15:38.638 --> 15:41.639
Don't believe everything
you read in books, son.

15:43.043 --> 15:45.043
Why's that?

15:45.045 --> 15:46.644
Because the people that
write those things are

15:46.646 --> 15:50.281
only out for one thing.
What's that?

15:50.283 --> 15:52.216
Get kids like you
to buy 'em.

15:52.218 --> 15:55.186
<i>(SIGH)</i>
besides...

15:55.188 --> 15:58.022
shooter green wasn't as
fast as billy the kid.

15:58.024 --> 15:59.624
<i>TOMMY: he wasn't?</i>

15:59.626 --> 16:02.427
Heck, no.

16:02.429 --> 16:04.195
He was <i> faster.</i>

16:04.197 --> 16:05.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:05.999 --> 16:07.465
how do you
know that?

16:07.467 --> 16:09.400
Because I <i> knew</i> him.

16:09.402 --> 16:12.136
Well, I'd
better turn in.

16:12.138 --> 16:13.705
So soon, but
it's early.

16:13.707 --> 16:15.373
<i>SAM: (GROANS)</i>
I got a lot to do tomorrow.

16:15.375 --> 16:17.976
These old bones don't
recover like they used to.

16:17.978 --> 16:19.477
I think Mr. Barnes
has a good idea.

16:19.479 --> 16:20.611
You...

16:20.613 --> 16:22.246
should be in
bed as well.

16:22.248 --> 16:24.248
Mama, let me read just
five more minutes.

16:24.250 --> 16:26.017
<i>(SIGHS)</i>

16:26.019 --> 16:27.418
all right, five
more minutes.

16:27.420 --> 16:29.354
But not a second longer.

16:29.356 --> 16:31.189
Good night,
ma'am.

16:31.191 --> 16:34.058
You can...

16:34.060 --> 16:36.527
you can call me susan.

16:36.529 --> 16:38.496
Well, only if
you call me sam.

16:38.498 --> 16:40.698
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:40.700 --> 16:42.333
all right.

16:42.335 --> 16:44.402
Sam.

16:44.404 --> 16:46.337
All right,
susan.

16:47.407 --> 16:50.074
Don't let the
bed bugs bite ya.

16:55.615 --> 16:57.582
He seems like a
real nice fella.

16:58.752 --> 17:00.685
Yeah, seems.

17:01.788 --> 17:10.560
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:10.563 --> 17:13.031
<i>(EXHALES)</i>

17:13.032 --> 17:21.239
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:26.179 --> 17:32.150
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:32.152 --> 17:34.218
<i>(DOOR OPENS)</i>

17:34.220 --> 17:36.354
<i>(FOOT STEPS)</i>

17:36.356 --> 17:37.455
yes?

17:37.457 --> 17:39.157
You've got a
telegram.

17:39.159 --> 17:41.125
Not now, sally.
It's marked urgent.

17:41.127 --> 17:42.260
Urgent...
<i>(LAUGHS)</i>

17:42.262 --> 17:43.728
SALLY: yeah, it's
about some prison

17:43.730 --> 17:48.066
break over at the
arkansas federal prison.

17:48.068 --> 17:50.535
Let me take a look
at that sally.

17:50.537 --> 17:52.303
SALLY:
here you go.

17:52.305 --> 17:58.509
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:58.511 --> 18:01.579
humph, sally...

18:01.581 --> 18:03.214
cancel that lunch.

18:03.216 --> 18:05.683
I might be
gone a while.

18:05.685 --> 18:14.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:14.127 --> 18:15.526
<i>(DOOR SHUTS)</i>

18:15.528 --> 18:19.130
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:19.132 --> 18:20.698
<i>(CHAMBER SHUTS)</i>

18:20.700 --> 18:23.734
<i>(HAMMERING)</i>

18:23.736 --> 18:24.869
<i>(GRUNTING)</i>

18:24.871 --> 18:29.507
<i>(HAMMERING)</i>

18:29.509 --> 18:31.409
<i>(GRUNT)</i>

18:31.411 --> 18:34.278
SAM: hand me a
nail, will ya?

18:34.280 --> 18:36.347
Nail, hello?

18:36.349 --> 18:38.282
Hey?

18:41.121 --> 18:42.120
Sorry.

18:42.122 --> 18:43.721
<i>(NAILS CLATTERING)</i>

18:43.723 --> 18:45.389
something on
your mind?

18:45.391 --> 18:47.291
<i>(HAMMERING)</i>

18:47.293 --> 18:49.660
I was just thinking about
what you said last night.

18:51.331 --> 18:53.831
I mean, you really
knew shooter green?

18:55.902 --> 18:57.602
Yeah, I knew him.

18:59.205 --> 19:01.806
Didn't much like
him, though.

19:01.808 --> 19:03.641
He was cocky.

19:03.643 --> 19:06.577
Cocky people
get reckless.

19:06.579 --> 19:08.746
So he was
mean, then?

19:08.748 --> 19:10.915
No, reckless and mean
are two different things.

19:10.917 --> 19:12.917
How's that?

19:12.919 --> 19:16.621
Well, I know for a fact shooter
never set out to hurt anyone.

19:19.759 --> 19:23.628
Never set out to become an
outlaw either for that matter.

19:23.630 --> 19:25.396
What makes you
say that?

19:29.502 --> 19:31.669
Well, I was there...

19:31.671 --> 19:33.905
when shooter green came
to the town of tucson

19:33.907 --> 19:37.241
in the summer of 1887.

19:37.243 --> 19:39.644
The same summer
as the robbery.

19:39.646 --> 19:41.312
<i>SAM: the very same.</i>

19:41.314 --> 19:46.551
<i>♪ (WESTERN) ♪</i>

19:46.553 --> 19:52.223
<i>(GALLOPING)</i>

19:52.225 --> 20:02.233
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:02.235 --> 20:11.943
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:11.945 --> 20:14.612
<i>SAM: shooter was riding in
from the east.</i>

20:14.614 --> 20:16.614
<i>He had no family, no money...</i>

20:16.616 --> 20:20.284
<i>and no possessions, except
his horse named trapper.</i>

20:20.286 --> 20:22.820
<i>And his six-shooter he
always kept on him.</i>

20:22.822 --> 20:24.889
<i>TOMMY: what happened
to his parents?</i>

20:24.891 --> 20:26.791
<i>SAM: don't know.</i>

20:26.793 --> 20:28.526
<i>Shooter always said that he
was found at the doorstep</i>

20:28.528 --> 20:32.597
<i>of a church, no note,
no name, nothing.</i>

20:32.599 --> 20:35.566
<i>But shooter was ready
to take on the world.</i>

20:35.568 --> 20:37.635
<i>Tucson would be the first stop.</i>

20:37.637 --> 20:47.645
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:47.647 --> 20:56.654
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:56.656 --> 21:00.591
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:00.593 --> 21:02.760
<i>he arrived in june of
that year and quickly</i>

21:02.762 --> 21:05.329
<i>got himself acclimated.</i>

21:07.367 --> 21:10.601
<i>He had come from kansas with
the hopes of staking a claim.</i>

21:10.603 --> 21:13.271
<i>But, to do that...</i>

21:13.273 --> 21:14.872
<i>he needed money.</i>

21:16.276 --> 21:17.808
<i>(BOTTLE SHATTERS)</i>

21:20.647 --> 21:24.715
<i>you see, while shooter knew he
was the fastest gun around...</i>

21:24.717 --> 21:27.718
<i>(SHOOTING)</i>

21:27.720 --> 21:30.488
<i>no one else in tucson did.</i>

21:30.490 --> 21:31.589
SHOOTER GREEN: so y'all
like what you see so far?

21:31.591 --> 21:33.424
<i>Yeah, it's pretty good.</i>

21:33.426 --> 21:35.493
<i>SHOOTER GREEN: all right,
here comes a tricky one.</i>

21:35.495 --> 21:36.394
You see this?

21:36.396 --> 21:37.862
Huh?

21:37.864 --> 21:38.829
I'm gonna flick it up
in the air and I'm gonna

21:38.831 --> 21:40.531
shoot it with my pistol.

21:40.533 --> 21:41.832
<i>(CROWD LAUGHING)</i>

21:41.834 --> 21:43.768
what do you think is so
funny over there, huh?

21:43.770 --> 21:45.469
You don't think I can do it? No.

21:45.471 --> 21:46.837
No way, young feller.

21:46.839 --> 21:48.406
<i>(FLICK, GUN SHOT)</i>

21:48.408 --> 21:49.507
<i>(GASP)</i>

21:49.509 --> 21:50.808
<i>(CLANK)</i>

21:50.810 --> 21:52.977
<i>(APPLAUSE)</i>

21:52.979 --> 21:55.379
SHOOTER GREEN: come on.

21:55.381 --> 21:56.847
Thank you.

21:56.849 --> 21:58.683
Thank you very much.

21:58.685 --> 22:00.051
I see some
sour faces.

22:00.053 --> 22:01.986
I appreciate it.

22:01.988 --> 22:04.955
This hat sure
appreciates it.

22:04.957 --> 22:10.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:10.930 --> 22:12.596
come on now,
further.

22:12.598 --> 22:20.805
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:20.807 --> 22:23.541
all right, now
we're talking.

22:23.543 --> 22:25.876
Yeah, yeah
right there.

22:25.878 --> 22:28.713
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:28.715 --> 22:30.414
<i>(CLANK)</i>

22:31.718 --> 22:33.484
all right.

22:37.457 --> 22:39.390
My name's shooter green.

22:40.827 --> 22:45.529
I can shoot the flea off
a dog from 50 yards.

22:45.531 --> 22:48.132
I can put a bullet through
the eye of a needle.

22:48.134 --> 22:49.967
You know what else?

22:49.969 --> 22:52.503
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:52.505 --> 22:55.139
I strike faster
than a rattlesnake.

22:55.141 --> 22:56.807
Hmm.

22:56.809 --> 22:58.943
Yeah...

22:58.945 --> 23:01.479
a Miss pays
three to one.

23:01.481 --> 23:02.780
Anybody
interested?

23:02.782 --> 23:05.049
<i>(PEOPLE CHATTERING)</i>

23:05.051 --> 23:06.550
you interested?

23:06.552 --> 23:07.885
You sure?
<i>MAN: yeah.</i>

23:07.887 --> 23:09.954
Yeah? All right.

23:09.956 --> 23:11.789
<i>(COCK GUN)</i>
I got 50.

23:13.459 --> 23:15.593
Whoa.
Got enough to cover a bet like that?

23:15.595 --> 23:19.029
<i>SAM BARNES, V/O: and then,
Miss josie hayes arrived.</i>

23:19.031 --> 23:21.031
Sweetheart,
I got plenty.

23:21.033 --> 23:22.867
<i>TOMMY, V/O: what
about Miss hayes?</i>

23:22.869 --> 23:24.502
All right then...

23:24.504 --> 23:26.036
consider me in.

23:26.038 --> 23:27.571
<i>SAM BARNES, V/O:
josie hayes was special.</i>

23:27.573 --> 23:29.507
<i>Shooter knew it right away.</i>

23:29.509 --> 23:31.008
Your money.

23:33.012 --> 23:35.913
<i>SAM BARNES, V/O: some say
it was a red-tailed hawk.</i>

23:35.915 --> 23:38.516
<i>Others say josie put
a spell on shooter.</i>

23:38.518 --> 23:39.984
<i>But, shooter...</i>

23:39.986 --> 23:41.552
<i>well...
(BIRD SQUAWKS)</i>

23:41.554 --> 23:43.087
<i>(GUN SHOT)</i>

23:44.991 --> 23:46.724
<i>it was the only time in
recorded history that</i>

23:46.726 --> 23:49.493
<i>shooter missed a shot.
(CLEARS THROAT)</i>

23:49.495 --> 23:51.128
<i>SAM BARNES, V/O: as
well as lost a bet.</i>

23:51.130 --> 23:54.632
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:54.634 --> 23:56.133
JOSIE: sure you
got enough?

23:56.135 --> 23:57.535
Pay it off in trade
if you have to.

23:57.537 --> 23:59.003
SHOOTER GREEN:
no, I got it.

23:59.005 --> 24:01.038
Don't you worry your
pretty little head.

24:01.040 --> 24:04.775
I wouldn't have made
the bet if I didn't.

24:04.777 --> 24:08.512
140, 142, 145...

24:08.514 --> 24:09.680
that's enough.

24:09.682 --> 24:10.614
I said I
got enough.

24:10.616 --> 24:12.850
All right?
Okay.

24:12.852 --> 24:15.453
Yeah, 150.

24:15.455 --> 24:17.721
You can count
it if you like.

24:17.723 --> 24:19.523
That's all right,
I trust you.

24:19.525 --> 24:21.091
You seem like a
man of your word.

24:21.093 --> 24:22.693
<i>(CLEARS THROAT)</i>
well, I am.

24:22.695 --> 24:24.094
You can take that
to the bank with ya.

24:24.096 --> 24:26.630
Well, I intend to.
Good.

24:30.670 --> 24:33.103
Well, I better
get going.

24:33.105 --> 24:34.972
Hey wait.

24:34.974 --> 24:37.675
You got a name?
Hayes.

24:37.677 --> 24:39.243
Josie hayes.

24:39.245 --> 24:41.645
Josie hayes.

24:41.647 --> 24:44.148
Well, where
ya from?

24:44.150 --> 24:46.550
I live half a day's
ride down in tombstone.

24:46.552 --> 24:48.252
My daddy's a
banker there.

24:48.254 --> 24:50.521
Oh, that makes sense.

24:50.523 --> 24:52.223
I guess you really are
gonna take the money

24:52.225 --> 24:54.725
to the bank
then, aren't ya?

24:54.727 --> 24:57.061
I've got a long
ride ahead of me.

24:57.063 --> 24:58.596
Well, uh...

24:58.598 --> 25:00.030
did you ride down
here all by yourself?

25:00.032 --> 25:02.666
I mean...
Is something wrong with that?

25:02.668 --> 25:05.169
Well uh...
I mean...

25:05.171 --> 25:07.071
I guess it's
just that...

25:07.073 --> 25:08.772
just what?

25:08.774 --> 25:10.674
Women aren't supposed
to ride all by themselves,

25:10.676 --> 25:12.076
is that it?

25:12.078 --> 25:14.845
Well... No!

25:14.847 --> 25:17.248
I mean uh...
of course, yeah.

25:17.250 --> 25:19.016
It's fine, I guess.

25:19.018 --> 25:21.151
I didn't mean no offense.
Look here, Mr. Green.

25:21.153 --> 25:22.753
I might be a woman...

25:22.755 --> 25:24.955
but, I can take
care of myself.

25:24.957 --> 25:28.158
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:28.160 --> 25:29.293
<i>(COCKS GUN)</i>

25:29.295 --> 25:31.161
<i>(GUN SHOT, HITS CAN)</i>

25:34.000 --> 25:35.799
humph.

25:38.671 --> 25:40.037
<i>SAM BARNES, V/O: yep,
shooter green had</i>

25:40.039 --> 25:41.972
<i>a masterful command of a gun.</i>

25:41.974 --> 25:43.941
<i>But, his heart?</i>

25:43.943 --> 25:47.177
<i>Well... That was another
matter all together.</i>

25:49.815 --> 25:52.883
<i>(TRAIN WHISTLING)</i>

26:00.326 --> 26:02.793
well howdy, Miss hayes.

26:02.795 --> 26:05.729
I was hoping I could
accompany you...

26:05.731 --> 26:07.598
on your ride back
to tombstone.

26:07.600 --> 26:08.999
Oh, for pete's sake.

26:09.001 --> 26:11.068
Don't you have anything
better to do?

26:11.070 --> 26:12.803
There's nowhere else in this
world I'd rather be right

26:12.805 --> 26:14.872
now than right here with you.

26:19.011 --> 26:20.644
<i>(CLEARS THROAT)</i>

26:20.646 --> 26:23.314
I'll tell ya, that was
some real sharp shooting

26:23.316 --> 26:25.349
you did back there.

26:25.351 --> 26:26.350
Who taught you?

26:26.352 --> 26:28.185
JOSIE: myself.

26:28.187 --> 26:30.354
You surprised?

26:30.356 --> 26:32.122
Truthfully?

26:32.124 --> 26:33.691
Yeah.

26:33.693 --> 26:35.960
Well, that's real
nice, ain't it?

26:35.962 --> 26:39.263
Listen Miss hayes, I don't
lie, not when it counts.

26:39.265 --> 26:41.832
And that's something
you'll learn about me.

26:41.834 --> 26:43.100
To...

26:43.102 --> 26:45.903
learn something
about someone...

26:45.905 --> 26:48.038
implies that you want to
be around them long enough

26:48.040 --> 26:49.907
to take any interest.

26:49.909 --> 26:52.309
What makes you think I want to
be around you long enough?

26:52.311 --> 26:53.877
I don't know.

26:53.879 --> 26:55.713
Maybe I just see
it in your eyes.

26:55.715 --> 26:57.114
Oh, is that a fact?

26:57.116 --> 26:58.849
And you want to know
what else is a fact?

26:58.851 --> 27:01.819
Reckon you're gonna
tell me anyway.

27:01.821 --> 27:03.854
Someday...

27:03.856 --> 27:06.090
I'm gonna make
you my wife.

27:06.092 --> 27:08.759
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:08.761 --> 27:10.294
<i>(LAUGHS)</i>

27:12.765 --> 27:15.032
well, to do that...

27:15.034 --> 27:17.368
you're gonna have
to catch me.

27:17.370 --> 27:19.703
<i>(HORSE NEIGHS)
(RIDING OFF)</i>

27:20.640 --> 27:21.905
<i>(LAUGHS)</i>

27:21.907 --> 27:27.411
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:27.413 --> 27:32.750
<i>(GALLOPING)</i>

27:32.752 --> 27:34.151
whoo hoo!

27:34.153 --> 27:35.686
All right!

27:35.688 --> 27:42.026
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:42.028 --> 27:50.067
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:50.069 --> 27:53.303
so shooter really was
that fast with a gun.

27:53.305 --> 27:55.706
SAM: sure was.

27:55.708 --> 27:59.910
I won and lost more money
on that boy's talents.

27:59.912 --> 28:01.945
And josie?

28:01.947 --> 28:04.181
How come the book
never mentions her?

28:04.183 --> 28:05.916
SAM: well...

28:05.918 --> 28:08.852
nobody really
knew about <i> her.</i>

28:08.854 --> 28:13.090
See their relationship
was kind of a secret.

28:13.092 --> 28:18.328
Her daddy was <i> the</i> big
man in those parts.

28:18.330 --> 28:23.000
Josie knew her daddy wouldn't
take too kindly to her courting

28:23.002 --> 28:26.470
a vagabond marksman from kansas.

28:26.472 --> 28:29.373
So, they kept their
relationship a secret.

28:29.375 --> 28:31.041
SAM: josie wanted
to tell her parents.

28:31.043 --> 28:33.944
She loved shooter
for who she was.

28:33.946 --> 28:35.813
She just...

28:35.815 --> 28:38.782
figured her parents
needed to accept that

28:38.784 --> 28:41.785
one way or another.

28:41.787 --> 28:44.288
Shooter on the other
hand, he figured...

28:44.290 --> 28:46.757
best be kept a secret till
he could afford to buy her

28:46.759 --> 28:50.194
a proper ring, proper wedding,
proper house, all the...

28:50.196 --> 28:52.329
<i>(SIGHS)</i>

28:52.331 --> 28:54.765
all the things a woman
of her upbringing

28:54.767 --> 28:57.000
had grown accustomed to.

28:57.002 --> 29:02.272
Shooter just couldn't get it
through his thick head that...

29:02.274 --> 29:05.509
josie loved him
for being him.

29:05.511 --> 29:08.412
<i>TOMMY: there's just one thing
I don't quite understand</i>

29:08.414 --> 29:10.881
<i>about all this
Mr. Barnes...</i>

29:13.986 --> 29:15.419
what's that?

29:15.421 --> 29:19.990
Well if their relationship
was supposed to be a secret,

29:19.992 --> 29:21.492
how come you knew about it?

29:21.494 --> 29:25.462
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:25.464 --> 29:30.300
now that is a
good question.

29:30.302 --> 29:31.802
I guess that uh-

29:31.804 --> 29:35.439
<i>SUSAN: lunch is ready!</i>

29:35.441 --> 29:37.307
I'm starved,
let's eat.

29:37.309 --> 29:39.943
<i>(LAUGHING)</i>
me too.

29:39.945 --> 29:42.946
<i>(ALL LAUGHING)</i>

29:42.948 --> 29:44.414
SAM: those sandwiches
were good, man.

29:44.416 --> 29:45.549
SUSAN: oh yeah,
mmm-hmm.

29:45.551 --> 29:47.551
Simple yet
satisfying.

29:47.553 --> 29:49.219
Sure was.

29:49.221 --> 29:51.321
Mr. Barnes here has been
telling me all about

29:51.323 --> 29:53.090
the outlaw shooter green.

29:53.092 --> 29:54.925
SUSAN: uh-huh.

29:54.927 --> 29:56.326
Is that a fact?

29:56.328 --> 29:57.961
SAM: yes ma'am.

29:57.963 --> 29:59.530
Mostly I was telling tommy
not to believe everything

29:59.532 --> 30:01.265
he reads in books.

30:01.267 --> 30:03.300
At least not those
types anyway.

30:03.302 --> 30:05.469
Well, I guess you
can blame me for that.

30:05.471 --> 30:07.805
I'm the one who let
him start reading them.

30:07.807 --> 30:13.143
Seems it's the only
thing he enjoys since...

30:13.145 --> 30:15.145
um...

30:18.117 --> 30:21.952
<i>(SILVERWARE CLANKING)</i>

30:21.954 --> 30:24.922
uh, clear your place.

30:24.924 --> 30:26.857
TOMMY:
yes sir.

30:26.859 --> 30:28.892
Here, we'll
help you out here.

30:28.894 --> 30:30.360
SUSAN: thank you.

30:30.362 --> 30:39.236
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:39.238 --> 30:48.612
<i>♪ (SUSPENSE) ♪</i>

30:48.614 --> 30:58.055
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:58.057 --> 31:08.031
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:08.033 --> 31:12.202
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:12.204 --> 31:14.638
yes?
<i>(CAR DOOR SHUTS)</i>

31:14.640 --> 31:16.406
I uh...
<i>(LAUGHS)</i>

31:16.408 --> 31:19.076
I don't mean to disturb
you ma'am, but uh...

31:19.078 --> 31:22.412
I'm looking for a couple
by the name of kineson.

31:22.414 --> 31:27.618
He was our family's minister
in tucson over 30 years ago.

31:27.620 --> 31:30.988
You got a second to talk?

31:30.990 --> 31:33.290
Well, I could use
a refreshment.

31:33.292 --> 31:35.025
Do you want to join
me on the porch?

31:35.027 --> 31:36.560
Thank you, ma'am.

31:38.497 --> 31:41.932
MARTHA: <i> (LAUGHS)</i>
don't get much company out here.

31:41.934 --> 31:44.434
Uh, thank you.

31:44.436 --> 31:45.435
<i>♪ (SUSPENSE) ♪</i>

31:45.437 --> 31:48.505
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:48.507 --> 31:50.507
so um...

31:50.509 --> 31:53.977
how long ago did
the kinesons pass?

31:53.979 --> 31:56.513
Oh, some years back.

31:56.515 --> 31:59.616
Just before
the war I think.

31:59.618 --> 32:01.485
Car accident.

32:03.489 --> 32:07.291
They uh, they had a
daughter didn't they?

32:07.293 --> 32:08.992
MARTHA:
yes, mm-hmm.

32:08.994 --> 32:11.595
Lives in kentucky near
as I can recollect.

32:11.597 --> 32:13.363
She married a
fella up there.

32:13.365 --> 32:16.533
Tilwicky,
darwin tilwicky.

32:16.535 --> 32:19.202
They sold
us this place.

32:19.204 --> 32:22.506
When it went on the
market we bought it.

32:22.508 --> 32:25.242
Oh, you going so soon?
Yes, ma'am.

32:25.244 --> 32:29.680
I'm not a race horse
and kentucky's...

32:29.682 --> 32:32.316
not getting any closer
with me sitting here.

32:32.318 --> 32:34.217
Well bye.

32:34.219 --> 32:41.058
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:41.060 --> 32:50.701
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:50.703 --> 32:53.971
<i>(FOOT STEPS,
FLOOR CREAKS)</i>

32:57.343 --> 32:59.142
you ever fired
a gun before?

33:00.079 --> 33:02.612
No sir.

33:02.614 --> 33:05.716
My pa kept promising
we would, but...

33:05.718 --> 33:09.119
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:09.121 --> 33:10.687
SAM: well, I
tell you what...

33:10.689 --> 33:13.590
after chores this morning,
why don't we give it a try?

33:13.592 --> 33:15.192
That is, if it's
okay with your mom.

33:16.462 --> 33:18.362
What's that?

33:18.364 --> 33:23.133
Mr. Barnes wants to teach
me to shoot after chores!

33:23.135 --> 33:24.601
Can we mama, please?

33:24.603 --> 33:26.336
Boy should learn to
protect his family.

33:26.338 --> 33:28.772
<i>If you don't
mind my saying.</i>

33:28.774 --> 33:31.575
In fact, I
<i>do</i> mind, sam.

33:31.577 --> 33:33.010
A gun is
not a toy.

33:33.012 --> 33:34.211
Mama, I'm
nearly 11-

33:34.213 --> 33:36.346
listen to your
mama, tommy.

33:36.348 --> 33:37.514
I should've
consulted her.

33:37.516 --> 33:39.583
I overstepped;
I apologize.

33:42.554 --> 33:44.554
<i>(SIGHS)</i>

33:44.556 --> 33:47.224
ah, it's all right.

33:47.226 --> 33:49.426
This business at the bank has
just got me a little stressed.

33:49.428 --> 33:52.162
That's all.

33:52.164 --> 33:54.531
His pa was gonna teach
him how to shoot and...

33:54.533 --> 33:56.600
tommy shouldn't have
to suffer just because

33:56.602 --> 33:59.302
he's not around
here to do that.

33:59.304 --> 34:01.238
<i>TOMMY: that mean
he can teach me?</i>

34:01.240 --> 34:02.773
Does it, mama?

34:02.775 --> 34:07.377
I suppose so, providing
you get your chores done.

34:07.379 --> 34:09.112
Okay, okay
mama I will!

34:09.114 --> 34:10.547
I'll start right now!

34:11.483 --> 34:13.050
Uh...
<i>(RUNNING STEPS)</i>

34:13.052 --> 34:14.418
hey paps,
it's chore time!

34:14.420 --> 34:16.353
<i>(DOG BARKS)</i>

34:16.355 --> 34:18.554
<i>(SIGHS)</i>

34:18.556 --> 34:20.757
you promise me
you'll keep him safe.

34:20.759 --> 34:23.793
Oh, you
have my word.

34:23.795 --> 34:25.295
Thank you, sam.

34:25.297 --> 34:30.734
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:30.735 --> 34:32.835
good luck.

34:34.739 --> 34:39.643
<i>(TYPEWRITER)</i>

34:39.645 --> 34:41.078
<i>SUSAN: my husband
always dealt with</i>

34:41.080 --> 34:43.679
<i>the business side of things.</i>

34:43.681 --> 34:47.117
The farm has been in his
family for generations.

34:47.119 --> 34:48.618
Yes, I...

34:48.620 --> 34:51.254
was sorry to hear
of his passing.

34:51.255 --> 34:53.123
Thank you.

34:53.125 --> 34:57.427
There's no delicate way to
put this Mrs. Tilwicky, so...

34:57.429 --> 34:59.663
I'm just gonna
come out with it.

34:59.665 --> 35:02.732
The bank has petitioned your
property for foreclosure.

35:04.803 --> 35:07.804
What exactly
does that mean?

35:07.806 --> 35:10.107
MR. DAVIS:
well...

35:10.109 --> 35:13.577
you'll have till the end of
the month to either bring

35:13.579 --> 35:19.116
the loan current or remove your
belongings from the premises.

35:19.118 --> 35:21.551
Anything left will be
sold at auction two weeks

35:21.553 --> 35:23.220
later with the property.

35:24.857 --> 35:26.756
But the horse auction's
not for another three months.

35:26.758 --> 35:28.225
We don't-

35:28.227 --> 35:29.759
we don't have
enough time.

35:29.761 --> 35:31.461
Without broke horses we
won't get a good enough price.

35:31.463 --> 35:35.398
MR. DAVIS:
I'm sorry, but...

35:35.400 --> 35:37.267
but policy is
policy, ma'am.

35:37.269 --> 35:41.805
SUSAN: my husband put everything
he had into that farm.

35:41.807 --> 35:44.808
And he fought in the war
for our country.

35:44.810 --> 35:48.378
And somehow we managed
to hang onto it.

35:48.380 --> 35:50.747
But, if you take that
farm away from us,

35:50.749 --> 35:53.383
that's all we got
left of him.

35:53.385 --> 35:56.319
So I'm just asking you
please, please can you

35:56.321 --> 35:57.521
just give us six more months?

35:57.523 --> 35:58.889
I can get you the
money in six months.

35:58.891 --> 36:00.590
MR. DAVIS:
Mrs. Tilwicky...

36:00.592 --> 36:02.192
please.

36:02.194 --> 36:05.195
I'm really sorry, but
the bank's done...

36:05.197 --> 36:06.897
done all we
can do, ma'am.

36:06.899 --> 36:10.233
<i>♪ (SOMBER) ♪</i>

36:10.235 --> 36:14.504
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:14.506 --> 36:16.540
thank you
for your time.

36:16.542 --> 36:19.676
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:19.678 --> 36:22.679
<i>(SNIFFLING)</i>

36:22.681 --> 36:29.686
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:29.688 --> 36:38.428
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:38.430 --> 36:40.197
<i>(GUN SHOT)</i>

36:40.933 --> 36:42.966
good shot,
mr. Barnes!

36:44.603 --> 36:46.303
All right, it's gonna
be your turn now.

36:46.305 --> 36:47.704
I'm gonna hand
you this weapon.

36:47.706 --> 36:49.206
You're gonna take a
nice, firm grip on it.

36:49.208 --> 36:50.407
You grab that, grab
it right there.

36:50.409 --> 36:51.841
You got it good?
Uh-huh.

36:51.843 --> 36:53.443
Put that into your
shoulder, nice and tight.

36:53.445 --> 36:54.711
You've read about
this stuff, haven't you?

36:54.713 --> 36:56.279
Yes, sir.

36:56.281 --> 36:57.581
Put your other hand
out there, cradle it.

36:57.583 --> 36:59.216
Hold it
carefully.

36:59.218 --> 37:00.483
All right...

37:00.485 --> 37:02.452
now, I'm gonna
rack a load.

37:02.454 --> 37:04.654
Hand under there?
Good, all right.

37:04.656 --> 37:07.290
Don't put your finger
on the trigger yet, okay?

37:07.292 --> 37:09.626
Now, you're gonna want to
look through this sight here.

37:09.628 --> 37:11.428
Uh-huh...
On that front sight.

37:11.430 --> 37:12.462
Keep your eye
focused on

37:12.464 --> 37:13.563
that front sight.

37:13.565 --> 37:14.831
You put it on one
of those apples.

37:14.833 --> 37:16.399
You're gonna remember
three things.

37:16.401 --> 37:18.301
Nice balance.

37:18.303 --> 37:20.003
Take a nice,
deep breath.

37:20.005 --> 37:22.906
<i>(BREATHING)</i>
let it go, relax.

37:22.908 --> 37:25.342
And gently pull
that trigger.

37:27.012 --> 37:28.878
<i>(GUN SHOT)</i>

37:29.815 --> 37:31.448
nuts!

37:31.450 --> 37:32.916
It's all right,
that's all right.

37:32.918 --> 37:34.751
Let's try again.

37:34.753 --> 37:36.253
Finger off
that trigger.

37:36.255 --> 37:39.289
Okay, get it up
against your shoulder.

37:39.291 --> 37:41.925
Front sight.
<i>(EXHALES)</i>

37:41.927 --> 37:46.296
balance, breathing.
<i>(BOTH BREATHING)</i>

37:48.033 --> 37:50.467
gently pull
that trigger.

37:50.469 --> 37:53.336
<i>(EXHALES)</i>

37:55.374 --> 37:57.674
<i>(GUN SHOT)</i>

37:57.676 --> 37:58.808
I hit it!

37:58.810 --> 38:00.677
SAM: you're a good
shot, tommy.

38:00.679 --> 38:02.345
Just might be as good
as shooter one day.

38:02.347 --> 38:06.349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:06.351 --> 38:07.984
<i>(DOOR OPENS,
FEET SCAMPER)</i>

38:07.986 --> 38:09.653
mama, mama
I did it!

38:09.655 --> 38:10.920
I shot a piece of fruit!

38:10.922 --> 38:13.490
It was a...
uh...

38:13.492 --> 38:15.558
what was it you
called it again?

38:15.560 --> 38:17.627
A hundred-yard shot.

38:17.629 --> 38:19.896
Yeah, yeah a
hundred-yard shot.

38:19.898 --> 38:21.998
<i>(IMITATES GUN SHOT)</i>

38:22.000 --> 38:25.068
that's-- that's good.

38:25.070 --> 38:28.605
That's real
good, tommy.

38:28.607 --> 38:30.373
Tommy, why don't you
go get washed up?

38:30.375 --> 38:34.044
I'll teach you how to
clean that after we eat.

38:34.046 --> 38:36.413
TOMMY: okay,
yes sir.

38:36.415 --> 38:38.548
SAM: go on.

38:38.550 --> 38:41.951
<i>(RUNNING FOOTSTEPS)</i>

38:41.953 --> 38:44.321
bank wouldn't budge?

38:45.891 --> 38:47.724
No...

38:47.726 --> 38:50.760
not even
a little.

38:52.698 --> 38:56.333
<i>(CRYING)</i> I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

38:56.335 --> 38:58.601
Well, it's gonna
be okay.

38:58.603 --> 39:00.904
It's all gonna
work out.

39:00.906 --> 39:02.405
You'll see.

39:02.407 --> 39:07.077
<i>(CRYING)</i>

39:07.079 --> 39:09.646
what you need to do is
stay strong for that boy.

39:09.648 --> 39:10.847
Okay?

39:10.849 --> 39:12.515
SUSAN:
you're right.

39:12.517 --> 39:13.717
You're right.

39:13.719 --> 39:14.818
SAM: I'll mind tommy.

39:14.820 --> 39:17.020
You take as much
time as you need.

39:20.058 --> 39:23.126
Thank you, sam.

39:23.128 --> 39:24.761
It'll be fine.

39:24.763 --> 39:26.763
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:26.765 --> 39:36.740
<i>(WHISTLING)</i>

39:36.742 --> 39:40.510
hey, yesterday you were
gonna tell me how come...

39:40.512 --> 39:43.580
you knew so much
about shooter.

39:43.582 --> 39:44.914
I mean...

39:44.916 --> 39:47.450
seeing as he was
a loner and all.

39:48.387 --> 39:51.454
<i>(EXHALES)</i>
well...

39:51.456 --> 39:54.858
I guess you could say
I was sort of a...

39:54.860 --> 39:57.060
confidant of shooter's.

39:58.397 --> 40:00.630
What's that?
<i>SAM: confidant?</i>

40:00.632 --> 40:03.066
Someone he could
bounce things off of.

40:03.068 --> 40:05.034
Make sure he was doing
the right thing.

40:06.872 --> 40:10.740
Kind of like what we're doing right now.
<i>SAM: yeah.</i>

40:10.742 --> 40:12.809
Kind of like what
we're doing right now.

40:14.813 --> 40:17.580
<i>(WHISTLING)</i>

40:18.517 --> 40:20.583
TOMMY: so...

40:20.585 --> 40:23.520
what ended up happening
with shooter and josie?

40:23.522 --> 40:24.954
You're just not gonna
give up till you know

40:24.956 --> 40:26.189
everything, are ya?

40:26.191 --> 40:28.191
Nope.
<i>(SAM SIGHS)</i>

40:28.193 --> 40:31.161
let me see...
Where was I?

40:31.163 --> 40:33.730
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:33.732 --> 40:36.433
all right.

40:36.435 --> 40:37.901
Shooter and josie had
been secretly courting

40:37.903 --> 40:39.936
<i>for most of the summer and...</i>

40:39.938 --> 40:43.006
<i>he knew she was
the one for him.</i>

40:43.008 --> 40:45.875
<i>He also knew that if he was
gonna pop the question,</i>

40:45.877 --> 40:48.845
<i>he needed to get her a
proper engagement ring.</i>

40:48.847 --> 40:50.880
<i>At least to his
way of thinking.</i>

40:50.882 --> 40:52.949
<i>TOMMY: so, why didn't he
just raise more money</i>

40:52.951 --> 40:54.784
<i>from bets and shooting?</i>

40:54.786 --> 40:57.620
<i>SAM: that is a very good
question, young man.</i>

40:57.622 --> 40:59.989
<i>And it deserves a good answer.</i>

40:59.991 --> 41:08.631
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:08.633 --> 41:10.700
<i>(GUN SHOTS)</i>

41:14.673 --> 41:17.173
MAN: big deal,
seen it already.

41:17.175 --> 41:19.576
<i>SAM: under normal
circumstances...</i>

41:19.578 --> 41:21.544
<i>shooter would've simply
packed up and moved on to</i>

41:21.546 --> 41:23.546
<i>the next place that
hadn't heard of him.</i>

41:23.548 --> 41:25.782
<i>Now that he had
josie on his mind...</i>

41:25.784 --> 41:29.519
<i>leaving wasn't an option.</i>

41:29.521 --> 41:31.521
<i>TOMMY: what did
he end up doing?</i>

41:31.523 --> 41:35.592
<i>SAM: for a time, he sat around
and felt sorry for himself.</i>

41:35.594 --> 41:37.527
<i>That is...</i>

41:37.529 --> 41:38.928
<i>until one day.</i>

41:40.599 --> 41:42.031
<i>(GLASS CLINKS)</i>

41:43.969 --> 41:45.969
<i>♪ (SUSPENSE) ♪</i>

41:45.971 --> 41:55.578
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:55.580 --> 41:57.981
can I get you
anything, marshal?

41:57.983 --> 42:02.151
Yeah, I think I'll have a
nip of the old overhaul.

42:02.153 --> 42:04.020
Make it two.

42:08.860 --> 42:11.694
Word on the street
is that um...

42:11.696 --> 42:14.030
you've fallen
onto hard times.

42:14.032 --> 42:16.266
I ain't done nothing wrong,
if that's what you're asking.

42:16.268 --> 42:18.601
Oh, I ain't-I ain't
here to say you <i> did.</i>

42:18.603 --> 42:21.704
I'm just passing on my
findings, that's all.

42:21.706 --> 42:24.207
Just 'cause one man's
looking for another...

42:24.209 --> 42:28.044
doesn't mean it's
necessarily a bad thing.

42:31.049 --> 42:33.182
Virgil earp.

42:33.184 --> 42:35.118
Yeah, I've
heard of you.

42:35.120 --> 42:37.053
Is that so?
Uh-huh.

42:37.055 --> 42:38.855
You and your brother
made quite the name for

42:38.857 --> 42:40.790
yourselves down in kansas.

42:41.826 --> 42:43.226
What brings
you to tucson?

42:43.228 --> 42:45.895
VIRGIL: business for
the arizona territory.

42:45.897 --> 42:50.033
We're starting a series
of shipments weekly.

42:51.570 --> 42:52.769
Well...

42:52.771 --> 42:54.103
what's that got
to do with me?

42:54.105 --> 42:57.273
Well, I've heard that
you're spectacularly

42:57.275 --> 43:00.043
good with a gun.

43:00.045 --> 43:02.211
How so?

43:02.213 --> 43:04.080
VIRGIL: thank
you, ma'am.

43:04.082 --> 43:08.217
I need men to watch
over those shipments.

43:08.219 --> 43:11.621
Men I can trust to show
up and meet the stagecoach.

43:12.724 --> 43:16.693
These parts
aren't really...

43:16.695 --> 43:19.295
tamed, so to speak.

43:19.297 --> 43:22.699
There's a lot of unsavory
types that like to make

43:22.701 --> 43:26.869
a quick buck on the likes of
what's on those shipments.

43:28.807 --> 43:31.174
Well, what is the content
of those shipments?

43:31.176 --> 43:36.746
VIRGIL: that's for me to know
and you, my friend, to protect.

43:36.748 --> 43:38.381
What makes you think
I'd be interested?

43:38.383 --> 43:40.984
Oh, just $500.

43:42.354 --> 43:44.921
And more where that came
from, if you stay on

43:44.923 --> 43:47.156
beyond three months.

43:47.158 --> 43:48.625
Oh, you won't be
at it alone.

43:48.627 --> 43:49.826
There will be
others with you.

43:49.828 --> 43:50.994
But it won't be easy.

43:50.996 --> 43:54.297
There will be a
mark on your head.

43:54.299 --> 43:57.066
And I'm here to tell ya...

43:57.068 --> 43:59.869
shooting up fellas what
are shooting back...

44:01.673 --> 44:04.407
isn't as easy as
busting them bottles.

44:06.878 --> 44:10.847
I mean, it all sounds
pretty interesting.

44:10.849 --> 44:12.782
Can I give you an
answer in the morning?

44:12.784 --> 44:14.851
Oh, of course,
I understand.

44:14.853 --> 44:16.853
You gotta check in
with the little lady.

44:16.855 --> 44:19.689
She's a beauty.

44:19.691 --> 44:22.091
What do you know
about josie?

44:22.093 --> 44:24.227
I make it my business
to know everything about

44:24.229 --> 44:28.097
a man that I'm about to hire.

44:28.099 --> 44:30.967
You see, when you're
on that trail

44:30.969 --> 44:33.970
you're an extension
of myself.

44:33.972 --> 44:35.672
Anything...

44:37.075 --> 44:38.808
goes wrong out there...

44:38.810 --> 44:41.177
I will take it personal.

44:41.179 --> 44:44.147
You hear me?

44:44.149 --> 44:45.848
Yes sir.

44:47.452 --> 44:49.686
Good.

44:49.688 --> 44:53.723
Then, I expect you'll have an
answer for me in the morning.

44:53.725 --> 44:57.293
All right, then.

44:57.295 --> 44:59.028
You got
my word.

45:01.232 --> 45:03.166
<i>(FOOTSTEPS)</i>

45:03.168 --> 45:04.867
<i>SAM, V/O: now this left shooter
in a predicament.</i>

45:04.869 --> 45:06.803
<i>(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)</i>

45:06.805 --> 45:08.705
<i>he could either turn down the
job that would give him</i>

45:08.707 --> 45:10.173
<i>everything to
provide for josie...</i>

45:10.175 --> 45:12.175
<i>(GLASS THUDS ON TABLE)</i>

45:12.177 --> 45:15.211
<i>or tell josie he was about to
risk his life for somethin'</i>

45:15.213 --> 45:16.879
<i>she didn't even care about.</i>

45:16.881 --> 45:18.381
<i>TOMMY, V/O: let me guess...</i>

45:18.383 --> 45:20.450
<i>it didn't go over so
well did it?</i>

45:20.452 --> 45:23.319
<i>SAM, V/O:
uh... Nope.</i>

45:23.321 --> 45:26.823
Do you know what happens to
people that do that, shooter?

45:26.825 --> 45:28.458
They come back in
a pine box.

45:28.460 --> 45:30.993
And I know... I know.
I've seen it happen

45:30.995 --> 45:35.064
all the time with men my daddy
hired to bring one in and out.

45:35.066 --> 45:36.799
<i>(SIGHS)</i>

45:36.801 --> 45:39.802
well, I thought you'd
be thrilled.

